              "content": "# Async Trie Precalculation — Technical Design Document\n\n# 1. Glossary\n\n| # | Term | Definition |\n|---|------|-----------|\n| 1 | **State Root** | A 32-byte hash (B256) that cryptographically commits to the entire account/storage state of the chain. Computed by traversing the Merkle Patricia Trie. |\n| 2 | **Trie** | The Merkle Patricia Trie — a tree data structure used by Ethereum to store account state. Walking the full trie is expensive (100–500ms). |\n| 3 | **TrieUpdates** | Cached trie nodes from a previous computation. Feeding these into the next computation avoids re-walking unchanged paths. |\n| 4 | **HashedPostState** | The hashed representation of all account/storage changes. Input to the trie computation. |\n| 5 | **BundleState** | The cumulative EVM execution output — all account changes, storage changes, and contract creations up to a given point. |\n| 6 | **Flashblock** | A sub-block published every ~200ms during a 1-second block interval. Each flashblock includes a batch of transactions. A full block consists of multiple flashblocks (e.g., 5). |\n| 7 | **Resolve** | The moment when block building ends and the final payload (with correct state root) must be produced and sent to the consensus engine. |\n| 8 | **Cold Computation** | A full trie walk from scratch with no cached nodes. Slowest path (100–500ms). |\n| 9 | **Incremental Computation** | A trie walk that reuses cached nodes (TrieUpdates) from a prior computation. Only re-walks changed paths. Much faster (8–50ms). |\n| 10 | **Prefix Sets** | A compact representation of which trie paths have changed, guiding the trie walker to skip unchanged subtrees. |\n\n# 2. Background\n\nIn the flashblocks payload builder, a block is built incrementally across multiple flashblocks (typically 5 per 1-second block). During building, the state root in the payload header is set to `B256::ZERO` because computing the real state root is expensive.\n\nAt **resolve time** (when the consensus engine requests the final payload via `get_payload`), the builder must compute the correct state root for the cumulative state of all flashblocks. This computation is on the **critical path** — it blocks the payload from being delivered.\n\n**Key file:** `crates/builder/src/builders/flashblocks/payload.rs`\n\n# 3. Problem\n\n**State root computation at resolve time is the primary latency bottleneck in block production.**\n\n| # | Issue | Impact |\n|---|-------|--------|\n| 1 | Cold state root computation takes 100–500ms | Delays payload delivery to consensus engine |\n| 2 | All computation happens at resolve time — no parallelism | Wasted CPU time during flashblock building |\n| 3 | Flashblock intervals (~200ms each) are idle from a trie perspective | Opportunity for background work is missed |\n\nWithout optimization, every resolve pays the full cold computation cost:\n\n```\nMain loop:  [fb0] [fb1] [fb2] [fb3] [fb4] [resolve: cold trie 100-500ms]\nWorker:     (nothing)\n```\n\n# 4. Solution\n\n## 4.1 Architecture Overview\n\nA **background worker thread** computes trie state roots incrementally while the main loop builds flashblocks. At resolve time, the worker's precomputed result is reused directly — no recomputation needed.\n\n### Components\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│  Main Thread (flashblock loop)                                      │\n│                                                                     │\n│  [build fb0] ──► [build fb1] ──► [build fb2] ──► ... ──► [resolve] │\n│       │               │               │                      │      │\n│   Arc\u003cBundleState\u003e Arc\u003cBundleState\u003e  Arc\u003cBundleState\u003e        │      │\n│       │               │               │                      │      │\n│       ▼               ▼               ▼                      │      │\n│  ┌─────────┐    ┌─────────┐    ┌─────────┐                  │      │\n│  │ work_tx │───►│ work_tx │───►│ work_tx │                  │      │\n│  └─────────┘    └─────────┘    └─────────┘                  │      │\n│                                                              │      │\n│  ┌───────────────── std::sync::mpsc ────────────────────┐   │      │\n│  │                   Work Channel                        │   │      │\n│  └───────────────────────┬───────────────────────────────┘   │      │\n│                          │                                   │      │\n│                          ▼                                   │      │\n│  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │      │\n│  │  Background Worker Thread                             │   │      │\n│  │                                                       │   │      │\n│  │  [cold fb0] ──► [incremental fb1] ──► [incr fb2] ──► │   │      │\n│  │       │               │                    │          │   │      │\n│  │   TriePrecalcResult  TriePrecalcResult    ...         │   │      │\n│  │       │               │                    │          │   │      │\n│  └───────┼───────────────┼────────────────────┼──────────┘   │      │\n│          ▼               ▼                    ▼              │      │\n│  ┌───────────────── std::sync::mpsc ────────────────────┐   │      │\n│  │                  Result Channel                        │   │      │\n│  └───────────────────────┬───────────────────────────────┘   │      │\n│                          │                                   │      │\n│                          ▼                                   │      │\n│                    result_rx.recv_timeout() ◄─────────────────┘      │\n│                          │                                          │\n│                          ▼                                          │\n│                 Return worker's (state_root, trie_updates,          │\n│                          hashed_state) directly                     │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n### Numbered Workflow Steps\n\n| Step | Action | Thread | Detail |\n|------|--------|--------|--------|\n| 1 | Initialize pipeline | Main | Create `work_tx/work_rx` and `result_tx/result_rx` channels. Spawn worker with its own `StateProvider`. |\n| 2 | Build flashblock N | Main | Execute transactions, produce `Arc\u003cBundleState\u003e` snapshot. |\n| 3 | Send work item | Main | `work_tx.try_send(TriePrecalcWorkItem { flashblock_index, bundle_state })` |\n| 4 | Compute trie | Worker | First item: cold `state_root_with_updates`. Subsequent: incremental `state_root_from_nodes_with_updates` using previous `TrieUpdates`. |\n| 5 | Send result | Worker | `result_tx.send(TriePrecalcResult { state_root, trie_updates, hashed_state })` |\n| 6 | Repeat steps 2–5 | Both | Main builds next flashblock while worker computes trie for current one. |\n| 7 | Resolve triggered | Main | `rx.recv()` returns `Err` (channel closed by timer). |\n| 8 | Drop work_tx | Main | Signals worker that no more items are coming. |\n| 9 | Block-wait for result | Main | `result_rx.recv_timeout(30s)` until target flashblock result arrives. |\n| 10 | Return cached result | Main | `calculate_state_root_on_resolve` returns `(precalc.state_root, precalc.trie_updates, precalc.hashed_state)` directly. No recomputation. |\n\n## 4.2 Timeline Comparison\n\n### Without Async Trie Precalc (cold)\n\n```\nMain:    [fb0 200ms][fb1 200ms][fb2 200ms][fb3 200ms][fb4 200ms][resolve: cold 150ms]\nWorker:  (none)\n                                                                 |---- 150ms ----|\nTotal resolve latency: 150ms\n```\n\n### With Async Trie Precalc (incremental, fully overlapped)\n\n```\nMain:    [fb0 200ms][fb1 200ms][fb2 200ms][fb3 200ms][fb4 200ms][resolve: 0ms]\nWorker:       [cold fb0 120ms][incr fb1 30ms][incr fb2 30ms][incr fb3 30ms][incr fb4 30ms]\n                                                                            ↑ finished before resolve\nTotal resolve latency: 0ms (wait_ms=0)\n```\n\n### With Async Trie Precalc (incremental, partially overlapped)\n\n```\nMain:    [fb0 200ms][fb1 200ms][fb2 200ms][fb3 200ms][fb4 200ms][resolve: wait 40ms]\nWorker:       [cold fb0 120ms][incr fb1 30ms][incr fb2 30ms][incr fb3 30ms][--- incr fb4 80ms ---]\n                                                                            |overlap 40ms|wait 40ms|\nTotal resolve latency: 40ms (wait_ms=40)\n```\n\n## 4.3 Key Design Decisions\n\n### 1. Direct result reuse (no cross-provider recomputation)\n\nThe worker and main loop share the same `Arc\u003cBundleState\u003e` for each flashblock. This means the worker's computed `state_root` is exactly the state root that resolve needs. At resolve, we return the worker's result directly — no `state_root_from_nodes_with_updates` call.\n\n**Why:** An earlier approach tried to use the worker's `TrieUpdates` as a seed and recompute the state root via the resolve's own `StateProvider`. This produced **incorrect state roots** because trie nodes from one `StateProvider` instance are incompatible with another.\n\n### 2. Strict incremental eligibility\n\n```rust\nlet eligible_precalc =\n    precalc_result.filter(|p| p.flashblock_index + 1 == ctx.current_flashblock_index);\n```\n\nThe precalc result is only used if it corresponds to `current_flashblock_index - 1` (the immediately prior flashblock). If the worker fell behind or computed a stale index, the resolve falls back to cold.\n\n### 3. Worker processes every item sequentially (no skipping)\n\nThe worker processes every flashblock in order without skipping. Each computation feeds its `TrieUpdates` into the next, maintaining a strict incremental chain. Skipping would break the chain and force a cold restart.\n\n### 4. 30-second timeout on resolve wait\n\n```rust\nwhile let Ok(result) = pipeline.result_rx.recv_timeout(Duration::from_secs(30)) { ... }\n```\n\nPrevents indefinite blocking if the worker hangs. On timeout, resolve falls back to cold computation.\n\n## 4.4 Data Structures\n\n```mermaid\nclassDiagram\n    class AsyncTriePrecalcPipeline {\n        +result_rx: Receiver~TriePrecalcResult~\n        +work_tx: SyncSender~TriePrecalcWorkItem~\n    }\n    class TriePrecalcWorkItem {\n        +flashblock_index: u64\n        +bundle_state: Arc~BundleState~\n    }\n    class TriePrecalcResult {\n        +flashblock_index: u64\n        +state_root: B256\n        +trie_updates: Arc~TrieUpdates~\n        +hashed_state: HashedPostState\n    }\n    AsyncTriePrecalcPipeline --\u003e TriePrecalcWorkItem : sends via work_tx\n    AsyncTriePrecalcPipeline --\u003e TriePrecalcResult : receives via result_rx\n```\n\n## 4.5 Sequence Diagram\n\n```mermaid\nsequenceDiagram\n    participant M as Main Thread\n    participant W as Worker Thread\n    participant C as Consensus Engine\n\n    Note over M: Block building starts\n    M-\u003e\u003eM: 1. Build flashblock 0\n\n    M-\u003e\u003eW: 2. Send Arc\u003cBundleState\u003e for fb0\n    M-\u003e\u003eM: 3. Build flashblock 1\n    W-\u003e\u003eW: 4. Cold trie computation (fb0)\n    W--\u003e\u003eM: 5. TriePrecalcResult { state_root, trie_updates }\n\n    M-\u003e\u003eW: 6. Send Arc\u003cBundleState\u003e for fb1\n    M-\u003e\u003eM: 7. Build flashblock 2\n    W-\u003e\u003eW: 8. Incremental trie (fb1, using fb0's TrieUpdates)\n    W--\u003e\u003eM: 9. TriePrecalcResult\n\n    Note over M: ... repeat for fb2, fb3 ...\n\n    M-\u003e\u003eW: 10. Send Arc\u003cBundleState\u003e for fb4 (last)\n    C-\u003e\u003eM: 11. get_payload (channel closes)\n    M-\u003e\u003eM: 12. drop(work_tx)\n    M-\u003e\u003eM: 13. recv_timeout(30s) — wait for fb4 result\n    W-\u003e\u003eW: 14. Incremental trie (fb4)\n    W--\u003e\u003eM: 15. TriePrecalcResult { state_root for fb4 }\n\n    alt Worker result matches target\n        M-\u003e\u003eM: 16. Return (state_root, trie_updates, hashed_state) directly\n    else No matching result\n        M-\u003e\u003eM: 16. Fall back to cold computation\n    end\n\n    M-\u003e\u003eC: 17. Deliver sealed payload with state root\n```\n\n## 4.6 Configuration\n\n| # | Flag | Default | Env Var | Description |\n|---|------|---------|---------|-------------|\n| 1 | `--flashblocks.enable-async-trie-precalc` | `false` | `FLASHBLOCKS_ENABLE_ASYNC_TRIE_PRECALC` | Master switch. Also requires `disable_state_root=true`. |\n| 2 | `--flashblocks.async-trie-precalc-start-flashblock` | `1` | `FLASHBLOCKS_ASYNC_TRIE_PRECALC_START_FLASHBLOCK` | Which flashblock index to start sending work items from. Default 1 skips fb0 (which has little state). |\n\n## 4.7 Metrics and Observability\n\n| # | Metric | Type | Description |\n|---|--------|------|-------------|\n| 1 | `op_rbuilder_trie_precalc_duration` | Histogram | Worker-side: time to compute each flashblock's trie |\n| 2 | `op_rbuilder_state_root_calculation_duration` | Histogram | Resolve-side: `precalc_wait + calc_time` (total critical path) |\n| 3 | `op_rbuilder_state_root_calculation_gauge` | Gauge | Latest resolve total time |\n\n### Key log lines for comparing optimization\n\n| # | Log Message | Field | Meaning |\n|---|-------------|-------|---------|\n| 1 | `\"Async trie precalculation completed\"` | `duration_ms` | Full worker computation time for one flashblock |\n| 2 | `\"resolve_best_payload: precalc wait completed\"` | `wait_ms` | How long resolve blocked waiting for the worker |\n| 3 | `\"calculate_state_root_on_resolve timing\"` | `total_ms` | **The single comparable metric.** `precalc_wait_ms + calc_ms`. Compare this value with and without the flag. |\n| 4 | `\"calculate_state_root_on_resolve timing\"` | `method` | `\"incremental\"` (used worker result) or `\"cold\"` (full computation) |\n\n### How to interpret\n\n- **Flag OFF**: `total_ms` = full cold computation (100–500ms), `method=\"cold\"`\n- **Flag ON, worker finished in time**: `total_ms` = `wait_ms` only (~0–80ms), `method=\"incremental\"`\n- **Flag ON, worker too slow**: `total_ms` = `wait_ms` (up to 30s timeout) then cold fallback\n\n## 4.8 Failure Modes and Fallbacks\n\n| # | Failure | Behavior |\n|---|---------|----------|\n| 1 | Worker `StateProvider` creation fails | Pipeline not created. All resolves use cold path. |\n| 2 | Worker trie computation fails | Worker resets `prev_trie_updates` to `None`. Next item does cold. Chain resumes incrementally after. |\n| 3 | `work_tx.try_send` channel full | Work item dropped with warning. Worker continues with what it has. |\n| 4 | Worker disconnects (panic) | `precalc_pipeline` set to `None`. Resolve uses cold path. |\n| 5 | `recv_timeout` expires (30s) | Resolve uses whatever result was received (or `None`). Falls back to cold if no eligible result. |\n| 6 | Precalc result flashblock index doesn't match | Eligibility check fails. Cold fallback. |\n",
